race.comment: Open contest. IMPOSANT (12) didn't measure up at Group 3 level two back before just running into one better at Doomben last time out. Is a two-time winner over this distance range and looks very hard to beat in this suitable race. HEMAN (4) looked handy winning at Doomben when resuming and will have derived some benefit from that first-up victory. Can go back-to-back. LITTLE JEANIE (14) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and looks a must for the exotics players from the low draw. ROCK HARD LOVE (6) is one from one over this course and distance and will strip fitter second-up from the break. Should be about the money. ENCUBIERTO (2) has won two of his past three and shouldn't be underestimated.
